rhetorical 中文翻譯
音標：[ ri'tɔrikəl ]  發音：  
中文翻譯手機版adj.(符合)修辭學的，修辭上的；華麗的，誇張的(文風)。 a rhetorical question 修辭性疑問(句)，(不期望得到回答的)反問，反詰〔例如：Who cares (＝Nobody cares)〕。adv.-ly a rhetorical question:    反問句rhetorical devices:    修辭手法rhetorical purpose:    修辭目的題rhetorical purposes:    修辭目的rhetorical question:    反問; 修辭問句; 修辭性疑問; 修飾性問句rhetorical school:    修辭學校rhetorical skill:    口齒伶俐; 修辭技能rhetorical structure:    修辭結構diverse ways for rhetorical emphasis:    英語修辭學中強調途徑多樣性的探討phonological rhetorical devices:    修辭格rhetorical uses of modeling elements:    電腦空間的造型元素to ask a rhetorical question:    以反問結尾rhetoric and english writing:    修辭與英語寫作rhetoric:    n. 修辭學；辯論法；雄辯術；華麗的文詞；花言巧語；辯才；修辭學書。 rhetor:    n. 〔古希臘〕修辭學教師[大師]；雄辯家，演說家。 rhetiques alpes:    雷蒂亞山脈rheticus:    雷蒂庫斯
例句與用法The grand design reached its rhetorical apogee .宏偉計劃達到口頭上的高潮。No one could have been adequate to so rhetorical a conception .沒有誰能夠適應這樣一種賣弄誇張的設計構思。It is a style which i have deliberately abandoned as too rhetorical .這種文體風格我因為它過分藻飾華麗已經存心放棄了。If i am rhetorical it was because stroeve was rhetorical .如果我在這里有些舞文弄墨，這是因為施特略夫當時就是這麽表達他自己的。That was for the splendours of the recent past; and for rhetorical and ornamental language .那是對往日繁華的嚮往以及對於修辭和華麗辭藻的愛好。This is for the splendours of the recent past, and for rhetorical and ornamental language .這是由於對往日繁華的嚮往以及對於修辭和華麗辭藻的愛好。Her rather rhetorical view of housing and its relation to the shape of society was incomplete .她相當浮誇的房屋政策及其與社會形態關系的觀點是不完善的。On the rhetorical method of liangshang folk songs涼山民歌歌詞的修辭方式之管見I ' m going to assume that was a rhetorical question我會假設這只是個修飾性問題。 Well , i guess - - - bro , it was a rhetorical question我覺得-兄弟，我這是反問句更多例句：  1  2  3  4  5用"rhetorical"造句  
英文解釋given to rhetoric, emphasizing style at the expense of thought; "mere rhetorical frippery"of or relating to rhetoric; "accepted two or three verbal and rhetorical changes I suggested"- W.A.White; "the rhetorical sin of the meaningless variation"- Lewis Mumford



